The use of linear threshold functions and polynomial threshold functions suggests a connection to machine learning and neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves analyzing the size of decision lists, which can be related to data structures (cs.DS). The use of spectral classes and polynomial threshold function classes suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
